And . . . nevermind!  The WinRar choice wasn't showing up for me when I right-clicked on the file.  If that happens to you, try navigating to the WinRar program on your computer, and using the WinRar menu to open up the download folder and then clicking on the .001 file inside the WinRar window.  After a second of thinking, it should open up to show you an ISO file.  Double click on that, and it will begin to extract.
